{"id": 3863, "title": "Ticket #3863: DAGMan shouldn't set logging flags when updating its job ad", "description": "<blockquote>\nWhen DAGMan periodically updates its job ad with stats about state of the DAG, it uses the SETDIRTY and SHOULDLOG flags with SetAttribute(). This causes the schedd to write events about the changes to the job log and attempt to notify DAGMan of the changes (unsuccessfully). Neither of these actions is necessary or appropriate.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2013-Sep-19 10:23</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/a340bb9b4d6c1b89cae0f503c356fd821f028433\">[37670]</a></span>: minor edit of 8.0.3 version history item <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=3863\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('3863'); return false;\" title=\"DAGMan shouldn't set logging flags when updating its job ad\">#3863</a></span>  (By Karen Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2013-Sep-11 17:10</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/4e4f5a068af91a865870c34fc0a10aace316a26b\">[37559]</a></span>: Version history for DAGMan ad updates resulting in user log events. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=3863\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('3863'); return false;\" title=\"DAGMan shouldn't set logging flags when updating its job ad\">#3863</a></span>  (By Jaime Fr